8,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"On the very first run against a fresh database, the _migrations table is created before any migration file is applied.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is initialization ordering across runner components (bootstrap metadata table -> apply migration files). Unit is too low because it depends on interaction between init and apply paths. System was considered and rejected: no behavior text requires OS/network/subprocess-specific phenomena; deterministic local integration with a fresh DB catches real ordering failures. No AI dependency.","test_description":"Start with a fresh database lacking _migrations, run the runner with at least one migration file, and verify _migrations is created before migration execution/recording (e.g., by asserting successful insert into _migrations occurs as part of first migration lifecycle without prior table errors).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}}]}
